1
00:01:49,509 --> 00:01:54,910
[A Dream Within A Dream]

2
00:01:55,009 --> 00:01:57,960
[Episode 29]

3
00:01:58,070 --> 00:02:01,730
[Pure of Heart]

4
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,329
Have you figured it out?

5
00:02:29,710 --> 00:02:30,520
Your Majesty,

6
00:02:31,630 --> 00:02:33,840
I've been working really hard,

7
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:36,360
following your every order to the letter.

8
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:37,360
For Great Jing

9
00:02:37,630 --> 00:02:38,750
and the people,

10
00:02:39,190 --> 00:02:40,720
I've always given it my all.

11
00:02:40,910 --> 00:02:41,840
I don't know

12
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:45,079
what I've done wrong.

13
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:49,150
Minister Yan,

14
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:51,360
His Majesty has always forbidden

15
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:53,420
forming factions for personal gain.

16
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:56,020
Your Majesty, I've never done that!

17
00:02:56,020 --> 00:02:59,180
[Petition]

18
00:02:56,960 --> 00:02:58,220
Today, I'm not going to

19
00:02:59,590 --> 00:03:02,400
dig into your family's past.

20
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:05,030
Who you once colluded with

21
00:03:05,430 --> 00:03:06,960
and what you did—

22
00:03:08,190 --> 00:03:09,250
it doesn't matter.

23
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,430
What I care about

24
00:03:11,630 --> 00:03:15,810
[Petition]

25
00:03:12,750 --> 00:03:15,550
is the result of
tomorrow's joint interrogation.

26
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:17,430
Tomorrow,

27
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:20,320
the Pingrong Battle case will be heard.

28
00:03:20,750 --> 00:03:23,000
I'll handle it impartially

29
00:03:24,190 --> 00:03:26,450
and present Your Majesty with the truth.

30
00:03:27,710 --> 00:03:29,000
The Pingrong Battle

31
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:31,840
was a tragedy for Great Jing.

32
00:03:32,590 --> 00:03:36,240
I do want justice for the people.

33
00:03:37,630 --> 00:03:38,240
But…

34
00:03:39,010 --> 00:03:39,790
[Memorial]

35
00:03:41,030 --> 00:03:43,520
it has to be the truth I want.

36
00:04:04,760 --> 00:04:05,890
Chancellor?

37
00:04:06,590 --> 00:04:07,430
You…

38
00:04:07,910 --> 00:04:09,360
Weren't you dead?

39
00:04:11,190 --> 00:04:12,590
Sorry to disappoint you.

40
00:04:12,850 --> 00:04:13,800
No, not at all.

41
00:04:13,980 --> 00:04:15,380
That's not what I meant.

42
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:20,089
Ever since I heard the news of your death,

43
00:04:20,190 --> 00:04:22,550
I haven't had a full night's sleep.

44
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,830
You guided me

45
00:04:24,830 --> 00:04:26,360
like a father.

46
00:04:26,430 --> 00:04:27,600
I've been

47
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:28,600
devastated

48
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:30,200
and overwhelmed with grief.

49
00:04:30,770 --> 00:04:32,300
I just wonder

50
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:35,600
what brought you back

51
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,830
and what all this is about.

52
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:45,780
I want you

53
00:04:46,130 --> 00:04:48,350
to testify against the Seventh Prince.

54
00:04:58,390 --> 00:04:59,790
What are you trying to do?

55
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:05,230
[Imperial Edict]

56
00:05:01,470 --> 00:05:03,800
His Majesty has ordered the Three Bureaus

57
00:05:04,040 --> 00:05:05,700
to investigate a murder case.

58
00:05:05,830 --> 00:05:06,820
Nan Heng

59
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:09,240
is a suspect in this case!

60
00:05:10,430 --> 00:05:11,240
You,

61
00:05:11,530 --> 00:05:13,950
go get your master out here.

62
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:16,040
He's coming with me
to the Ministry of Justice for trial.

63
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:17,040
You're too late.

64
00:05:17,430 --> 00:05:18,760
Our general isn't here.

65
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:19,920
Not here?

66
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:22,860
Don't play tricks.

67
00:05:23,190 --> 00:05:24,190
Where did he go?

68
00:05:24,570 --> 00:05:25,990
The Ministry of Justice.

69
00:05:27,430 --> 00:05:29,830
He knew about
today's joint interrogation?

70
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:32,110
There are no secrets under the sun.

71
00:05:35,070 --> 00:05:35,870
Fine then.

72
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:38,409
Since he's turned himself in,

73
00:05:38,750 --> 00:05:40,620
it saves me the trouble.

74
00:05:41,190 --> 00:05:42,390
Before the general left,

75
00:05:42,390 --> 00:05:44,250
he asked me to tell you something.

76
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:46,920
Go ahead.

77
00:05:47,890 --> 00:05:49,510
"If you want to frame someone,

78
00:05:49,510 --> 00:05:51,230
you'll always find a way."

79
00:05:55,300 --> 00:06:00,650
[Ministry of Justice]

80
00:05:58,120 --> 00:05:59,510
The joint interrogation today

81
00:05:59,510 --> 00:06:00,920
is actually for the Seventh Prince.

82
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:02,000
What has he done?

83
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:04,600
I heard that Capital Prefect Chu

84
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:06,480
discovered evidence
that the Seventh Prince

85
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:08,600
colluded with a traitor
during the Pingrong Battle.

86
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:10,500
If the prince can't prove his innocence,

87
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:12,170
he might lose his head.

88
00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:15,120
It's starting.

89
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:17,630
They're not letting us watch.

90
00:06:17,030 --> 00:06:19,930
[Justice Brings Clarity]

91
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:35,480
Nan Heng,

92
00:06:35,830 --> 00:06:37,390
as a murder suspect,

93
00:06:37,390 --> 00:06:38,830
you show no respect for the law,

94
00:06:38,830 --> 00:06:40,430
barging into the Ministry of Justice.

95
00:06:40,430 --> 00:06:41,720
What are you trying to do?

96
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:42,550
Chu Guihong,

97
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:45,000
as the capital prefect,

98
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:47,130
you fabricated false evidence

99
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:50,450
and forced confessions through torture.

100
00:06:51,010 --> 00:06:52,409
What are you trying to do?

101
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:55,560
Nan Heng,

102
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:58,970
where did these
bloodstained clothes come from?

103
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:02,310
The celestial prison.

104
00:07:02,740 --> 00:07:06,580
[One hour ago]

105
00:07:11,940 --> 00:07:12,860
Yunlong.

106
00:07:13,810 --> 00:07:14,620
Shanhu.

107
00:07:15,950 --> 00:07:16,750
Chief.

108
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:19,000
He tortured you?

109
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:20,650
Barely a tickle.

110
00:07:20,650 --> 00:07:21,850
Don't worry about it.

111
00:07:22,310 --> 00:07:22,950
I'm fine.

112
00:07:23,670 --> 00:07:25,540
That idiot Chu Guihong

113
00:07:25,830 --> 00:07:27,150
isn't much of a threat.

114
00:07:31,990 --> 00:07:32,790
Don't worry.

115
00:07:33,950 --> 00:07:35,550
Anyone who hurts my brothers

116
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:37,390
has to pay for it.

117
00:07:43,530 --> 00:07:45,409
Where are Yunlong and Shanhu?

118
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:48,600
I've sent them to a clinic for treatment.

119
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:50,920
You broke into the celestial prison,

120
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:52,120
and freed prisoners.

121
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,700
That's a capital offense.

122
00:07:54,710 --> 00:07:57,310
I won't run from any crime
I should be held responsible for.

123
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:58,760
But you, Chu Guihong,

124
00:07:58,890 --> 00:08:00,090
fabricated evidence

125
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:01,240
to frame me.

126
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:04,010
I don't want any citizen of Great Jing

127
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:06,040
to die because of schemes and plots.

128
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:09,750
Ministers,

129
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:12,260
the whole city is watching

130
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:14,280
the joint interrogation today.

131
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:16,020
If anyone

132
00:08:16,190 --> 00:08:19,190
dares to conceal the truth
about the Pingrong Battle,

133
00:08:19,430 --> 00:08:20,950
I'll execute them

134
00:08:20,980 --> 00:08:22,550
on the spot.

135
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,030
Wake up.

136
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:40,000
Your employer is here to get you.

137
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:46,090
Why are you running?

138
00:08:46,630 --> 00:08:47,910
I'm not here for you.

139
00:08:51,150 --> 00:08:52,410
Nan Heng is in trouble.

140
00:08:54,940 --> 00:08:55,850
Mr. Chu,

141
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:57,440
you accuse Nan Heng of ordering

142
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:59,860
the assassination of Lu Yi,
a scout from the Qianyu Army.

143
00:08:59,860 --> 00:09:01,140
Do you have proof?

144
00:09:06,630 --> 00:09:09,190
After Nan Heng learned that
I found the traitor Lu Yi,

145
00:09:09,190 --> 00:09:11,120
he was afraid that I'd find out
he colluded with Lu Yi

146
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:12,030
during the Pingrong Battle

147
00:09:12,030 --> 00:09:14,200
and concealed
the Qianyu Army's call for help.

148
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:16,860
So he sent his men
Yunlong and Shanhu to kill him.

149
00:09:17,180 --> 00:09:19,660
[Statement of Po Yunlong
from Waning River Crescent]

150
00:09:18,230 --> 00:09:20,760
These are Yunlong
and Shanhu's confessions.

151
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:24,500
Yunlong and Shanhu did not kill Lu Yi.

152
00:09:24,910 --> 00:09:25,910
This so-called evidence

153
00:09:25,910 --> 00:09:27,750
was forged by you, Chu Guihong.

154
00:09:28,230 --> 00:09:29,180
Those two

155
00:09:29,630 --> 00:09:31,760
were tortured by you into confessing.

156
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:34,030
The blood-stained clothes are the proof.

157
00:09:34,030 --> 00:09:36,030
Ministers, if you don't believe me,

158
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:37,630
you can summon them anytime

159
00:09:37,710 --> 00:09:39,270
for a face-to-face confrontation.

160
00:09:39,270 --> 00:09:40,510
They work for you.

161
00:09:41,210 --> 00:09:42,840
Naturally, they'll say whatever

162
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:43,770
you tell them to.

163
00:09:45,060 --> 00:09:47,000
If, as you claim,

164
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:49,070
they'll say whatever I tell them to,

165
00:09:49,070 --> 00:09:51,400
why would they have testified against me?

166
00:09:51,680 --> 00:09:53,390
That's enough to prove one of two things:

167
00:09:53,390 --> 00:09:54,150
either

168
00:09:54,150 --> 00:09:56,630
you forced
the confession through torture,

169
00:09:56,750 --> 00:09:57,550
or

170
00:09:57,790 --> 00:09:58,590
this evidence

171
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:00,720
was made up by you.

172
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:17,360
What are you looking for?

173
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:18,550
Evidence.

174
00:10:19,490 --> 00:10:21,840
These are all letters
Chu Guihong wrote you.

175
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:23,840
How would there be evidence in them?

176
00:10:29,270 --> 00:10:30,200
I found it.

177
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:32,200
"That brat Nan Heng

178
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,840
is now trapped in Youcheng.

179
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:36,200
My father has placed spies around him.

180
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:39,100
If he dares step out of line,

181
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,660
he'll be punished."

182
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:44,840
This letter

183
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:47,760
was written five days
before the Pingrong Battle.

184
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,750
Nan Heng's every move

185
00:10:49,750 --> 00:10:51,240
was being watched at that time.

186
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:52,790
How could he have
colluded with the traitor

187
00:10:52,790 --> 00:10:54,190
without getting caught?

188
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:57,030
I'm going to the Ministry of Justice

189
00:10:57,030 --> 00:10:57,960
to clear his name.

190
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:58,720
Yimeng,

191
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:00,840
a joint interrogation
isn't a small matter.

192
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:03,090
All the big names in court are there.

193
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:04,630
I once broke into an execution ground.

194
00:11:04,630 --> 00:11:06,000
You think I'd be scared of this?

195
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,460
Chu Guihong clearly wants

196
00:11:07,510 --> 00:11:09,910
Nan Heng to be sentenced
to death this time.

197
00:11:10,030 --> 00:11:11,630
If I don't help him,

198
00:11:11,910 --> 00:11:13,790
who else will believe he's innocent?

199
00:11:13,790 --> 00:11:15,240
I'll go to Waning River Crescent for help.

200
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:16,030
No.

201
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:18,440
We can't involve the Nightwalkers.

202
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,120
What Nan Heng needs

203
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:22,240
is justice and truth.

204
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:24,030
Mr. Song,

205
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:26,510
do you still remember the battle report

206
00:11:26,510 --> 00:11:27,910
for the Pingrong Battle?

207
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:30,840
How could I forget?

208
00:11:32,270 --> 00:11:33,670
In the 4th year of Xiyuan,

209
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:36,320
on November 2nd,

210
00:11:37,790 --> 00:11:39,960
the Heyuan army took 100 civilians

211
00:11:40,390 --> 00:11:42,200
from Xing City and Ji City hostage

212
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:44,000
and approached Pingrong City.

213
00:11:44,410 --> 00:11:48,270
[Pingrong City, the Third Border City]

214
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:48,240
Lord Qianyu led 20,000 soldiers

215
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:49,820
and fought fiercely for six days,

216
00:11:49,820 --> 00:11:51,620
but was trapped and outmatched.

217
00:11:52,890 --> 00:11:55,310
Later, Junior General Chu Guihong

218
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:58,640
led an elite force on a night raid
of the enemy camp,

219
00:11:58,690 --> 00:12:01,770
intending to kill their commander,
Fang Shiming.

220
00:12:03,310 --> 00:12:04,390
Unexpectedly,

221
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:06,610
he walked into an ambush

222
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:07,760
and was captured.

223
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:09,870
Kill!

224
00:12:09,960 --> 00:12:11,240
At dawn the next day,

225
00:12:11,560 --> 00:12:12,600
Fang Shiming

226
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:16,000
led 30,000 Heyuan soldiers
in a full assault.

227
00:12:16,040 --> 00:12:21,880
[Youcheng, the Fourth Border City]

228
00:12:16,510 --> 00:12:18,510
They pushed all the way to Youcheng.

229
00:12:23,550 --> 00:12:25,710
The Qianyu Army
was stationed along the border.

230
00:12:25,710 --> 00:12:27,170
Other than Pingrong City,

231
00:12:27,790 --> 00:12:29,720
why were the other two cities lost?

232
00:12:29,840 --> 00:12:30,970
Is there any record?

233
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:35,440
The Qianyu Army had 40,000 soldiers

234
00:12:35,630 --> 00:12:38,290
and couldn't defend
all cities at the same time.

235
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:40,510
Pingrong's terrain is open—

236
00:12:40,770 --> 00:12:42,270
easy to attack, hard to defend.

237
00:12:42,270 --> 00:12:44,670
So most of the troops
were stationed there.

238
00:12:45,150 --> 00:12:47,810
That left Xing City
and Ji City under-defended,

239
00:12:49,100 --> 00:12:51,730
and they were taken first.

240
00:12:52,910 --> 00:12:54,040
That's why I believe

241
00:12:54,830 --> 00:12:56,290
something doesn't add up.

242
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:58,440
What do you mean?

243
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:01,260
Military deployment was top secret,

244
00:13:01,740 --> 00:13:02,910
yet the Heyuan forces

245
00:13:02,910 --> 00:13:04,870
struck the weakest cities first

246
00:13:05,150 --> 00:13:08,600
as if they knew exactly where to hit.

247
00:13:08,750 --> 00:13:09,550
I believe

248
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:11,950
someone must have

249
00:13:12,030 --> 00:13:13,510
leaked the deployment information

250
00:13:13,510 --> 00:13:14,840
to Heyuan in advance.

251
00:13:16,520 --> 00:13:18,200
My father ran the army
with strict discipline.

252
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:20,530
There were no traitors in the Qianyu Army!

253
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:23,630
But wasn't the traitor Lu Yi
whom you keep mentioning

254
00:13:23,630 --> 00:13:25,480
a scout from the Qianyu Army?

255
00:13:29,020 --> 00:13:30,010
Your Highness,

256
00:13:30,790 --> 00:13:33,630
are you suggesting
Lu Yi was bribed by Heyuan?

257
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:36,330
That's what I thought at first.

258
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:38,360
But as a traitor,

259
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:40,570
he returned to the capital unnoticed,

260
00:13:40,570 --> 00:13:41,910
got settled,

261
00:13:41,910 --> 00:13:43,170
and walked away clean.

262
00:13:43,300 --> 00:13:45,430
I don't think he had that kind of power.

263
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:47,000
So I believe

264
00:13:47,550 --> 00:13:49,750
there must've been someone behind him.

265
00:13:50,060 --> 00:13:53,790
[Five days before the Pingrong Battle]

266
00:14:08,420 --> 00:14:10,310
[Deployment Map of the Four Border Cities]

267
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:22,600
This person

268
00:14:22,790 --> 00:14:25,750
not only leaked
Great Jing's military intel to Heyuan

269
00:14:25,750 --> 00:14:26,720
but also twisted the truth

270
00:14:26,720 --> 00:14:29,120
and manipulated people behind the scenes.

271
00:14:30,150 --> 00:14:31,510
Yet someone

272
00:14:31,580 --> 00:14:33,620
fell for his schemes

273
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:36,710
and willingly helped him
cover up the truth.

274
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:42,050
In the Great Jing Dynasty, who else

275
00:14:42,340 --> 00:14:43,600
could've pulled that off

276
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:45,000
other than you, Nan Heng?

277
00:14:54,750 --> 00:14:55,680
Who is this girl?

278
00:15:04,550 --> 00:15:05,360
You...

279
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:06,870
Father.

280
00:15:06,990 --> 00:15:08,350
Why are you guys here?

281
00:15:09,550 --> 00:15:10,360
Mr. Song,

282
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:12,330
this is your family matter.

283
00:15:12,910 --> 00:15:14,200
Handle it yourself.

284
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:15,080
You…

285
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:16,000
Minister Yan,

286
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:18,650
the Pingrong Battle
was a national tragedy.

287
00:15:18,650 --> 00:15:21,050
The people have the right
to know the truth.

288
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:22,440
Please, Minister Yan,

289
00:15:22,440 --> 00:15:23,390
let us in.

290
00:15:23,390 --> 00:15:24,390
Yes, let us in.

291
00:15:24,390 --> 00:15:25,510
Let us in!

292
00:15:25,510 --> 00:15:26,700
Let us in!

293
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:28,070
Let us in!

294
00:15:28,270 --> 00:15:29,270
Song.

295
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:30,510
Let us in!

296
00:15:30,510 --> 00:15:31,930
This isn't up to me.

297
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:34,320
You decide.

298
00:15:36,510 --> 00:15:37,320
Father.

299
00:15:43,130 --> 00:15:43,840
You...

300
00:15:43,840 --> 00:15:44,750
My ears.

301
00:15:44,750 --> 00:15:45,550
My ears hurt.

302
00:15:45,550 --> 00:15:46,460
Song.

303
00:15:47,030 --> 00:15:47,960
My ears!

304
00:15:50,060 --> 00:15:51,170
My eyes.

305
00:15:51,520 --> 00:15:52,540
I can't see!

306
00:15:52,690 --> 00:15:53,690
I can't see!

307
00:15:53,870 --> 00:15:54,550
My eyes!

308
00:15:54,550 --> 00:15:55,240
Follow me.

309
00:15:55,240 --> 00:15:55,870
Quick, quick!

310
00:15:55,870 --> 00:15:56,880
Check on me.

311
00:16:03,150 --> 00:16:04,000
Minister Yan,

312
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:06,000
what is going on here?

313
00:16:06,320 --> 00:16:07,650
What are you doing here?

314
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:10,700
I'm here for the truth.

315
00:16:10,840 --> 00:16:12,300
For justice and fairness.

316
00:16:15,390 --> 00:16:16,340
Song Yimeng,

317
00:16:16,630 --> 00:16:18,090
what evidence do you have?

318
00:16:18,660 --> 00:16:20,110
Present it now.

319
00:16:20,220 --> 00:16:21,610
[Diligence for the People]

320
00:16:27,360 --> 00:16:28,480
Everyone knows

321
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:31,600
I had been engaged to General Chu
since we were young.

322
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:33,240
And while he was at the border,

323
00:16:33,240 --> 00:16:34,370
he often wrote to me.

324
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:37,520
This letter in my hand

325
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:39,960
was written by him personally.

326
00:16:40,760 --> 00:16:41,770
General Chu,

327
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:43,510
do you mind

328
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:45,440
if I read it out loud?

329
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:56,260
Since you claim I wrote the letter,

330
00:16:56,960 --> 00:16:58,560
I should be the one to read it.

331
00:17:01,360 --> 00:17:02,150
Fine.

332
00:17:02,630 --> 00:17:04,410
With so many eyes watching you,

333
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:05,790
you'd better

334
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:07,530
read it exactly as written.

335
00:17:08,920 --> 00:17:10,270
"That brat Nan Heng

336
00:17:10,310 --> 00:17:11,640
is trapped in Youcheng.

337
00:17:11,890 --> 00:17:14,410
My father has placed spies around him.

338
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:16,550
If he dares step out of line,

339
00:17:16,829 --> 00:17:18,420
he'll be punished."

340
00:17:23,920 --> 00:17:24,720
Absurd!

341
00:17:25,480 --> 00:17:26,270
Yimeng,

342
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:28,200
when did you become someone

343
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:29,590
who'd make stuff up?

344
00:17:33,810 --> 00:17:35,340
I did not write this letter.

345
00:17:35,870 --> 00:17:36,800
It had to be him.

346
00:17:37,350 --> 00:17:37,880
Yeah,

347
00:17:37,880 --> 00:17:39,010
it must've been him!

348
00:17:39,440 --> 00:17:41,100
Who's telling the truth here?

349
00:17:41,110 --> 00:17:42,000
Chu Guihong,

350
00:17:42,920 --> 00:17:45,120
do you dare swear you didn't write this?

351
00:17:45,640 --> 00:17:46,770
Miss Song, may I ask—

352
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:49,060
when was this letter written?

353
00:17:52,580 --> 00:17:54,550
Five days before the Pingrong Battle.

354
00:17:54,550 --> 00:17:55,790
Before the battle,

355
00:17:55,790 --> 00:17:57,400
I injured my right hand during training.

356
00:17:57,400 --> 00:17:59,530
It didn't heal until the battle began.

357
00:17:59,550 --> 00:18:00,350
Everyone

358
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:02,110
in the Qianyu Army knows this.

359
00:18:02,110 --> 00:18:04,110
So how could I have written this letter?

360
00:18:04,110 --> 00:18:05,830
You're beyond redemption.

361
00:18:10,830 --> 00:18:11,880
Ministers,

362
00:18:12,240 --> 00:18:13,570
if you don't believe me,

363
00:18:13,640 --> 00:18:15,440
you can compare
the handwriting here and now.

364
00:18:15,440 --> 00:18:17,000
If I'm lying,

365
00:18:17,130 --> 00:18:18,310
I'll accept any punishment.

366
00:18:18,310 --> 00:18:19,070
Enough!

367
00:18:19,520 --> 00:18:20,550
To help Nan Heng,

368
00:18:20,550 --> 00:18:22,280
you've actually gone this far.

369
00:18:23,360 --> 00:18:24,720
The inspector my father
placed in Youcheng

370
00:18:24,720 --> 00:18:25,830
on His Majesty's orders

371
00:18:25,830 --> 00:18:27,030
was assassinated by Nan Heng

372
00:18:27,030 --> 00:18:28,240
the moment he arrived.

373
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:30,510
That's how the Qianyu Army
lost contact with Youcheng.

374
00:18:30,510 --> 00:18:32,620
So how could anyone
have been monitoring him?

375
00:18:32,620 --> 00:18:33,660
Chu Guihong,

376
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:35,240
that's utter nonsense!

377
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:36,200
You're lying!

378
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:36,920
Everyone,

379
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:40,240
the letter is fake,

380
00:18:40,960 --> 00:18:42,400
but Nan Heng's treacherous ambitions

381
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:44,150
have long been obvious.

382
00:18:44,590 --> 00:18:46,790
He betrayed the country, let the enemy in,

383
00:18:46,790 --> 00:18:48,310
and tried to use the Heyuan army

384
00:18:48,310 --> 00:18:50,710
to wipe out the Qianyu Army
once and for all.

385
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:52,200
You…

386
00:18:54,580 --> 00:18:57,040
[Diligence for the People]

387
00:18:55,790 --> 00:18:56,590
Listen to me.

388
00:18:56,590 --> 00:18:57,310
Go now.

389
00:18:57,440 --> 00:18:58,180
Nan Heng,

390
00:18:58,400 --> 00:18:59,750
the letter isn't forged.

391
00:18:59,750 --> 00:19:01,750
Of course I know you didn't forge it.

392
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:03,440
How dare he lie

393
00:19:03,460 --> 00:19:05,020
in front of everyone?

394
00:19:05,260 --> 00:19:07,860
That letter just revealed
his true character.

395
00:19:07,870 --> 00:19:09,200
For Yimeng,

396
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:11,060
it's not necessarily a bad thing.

397
00:19:12,110 --> 00:19:13,150
Minister Yan,

398
00:19:13,440 --> 00:19:15,590
the truth behind the Pingrong Battle
is clear now.

399
00:19:15,590 --> 00:19:17,030
You're the presiding judge today.

400
00:19:17,030 --> 00:19:18,890
Why haven't you issued a verdict?

401
00:19:19,030 --> 00:19:20,050
Or have you,

402
00:19:20,710 --> 00:19:22,280
like Miss Song,

403
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:26,240
also been threatened
by this sinister schemer?

404
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:27,700
If he were truly sinister,

405
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,060
you wouldn't be standing here today.

406
00:19:36,920 --> 00:19:37,640
Father!

407
00:19:37,010 --> 00:19:39,820
[Keep Calm]

408
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:38,400
Father!

409
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:38,920
No.

410
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:39,400
Eunuch Liu.

411
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:40,440
Wait a moment.

412
00:19:39,820 --> 00:19:42,130
[As Always]

413
00:19:40,440 --> 00:19:41,000
No, no.

414
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:41,510
Father,

415
00:19:41,510 --> 00:19:42,270
this isn't right!

416
00:19:42,270 --> 00:19:43,510
Father, Father!

417
00:19:43,510 --> 00:19:44,200
No, no!

418
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:45,310
Eunuch Liu, wait, wait!

419
00:19:45,310 --> 00:19:45,830
Stop!

420
00:19:45,830 --> 00:19:46,590
You…

421
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:48,960
Rui.

422
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:51,000
What are you doing?

423
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:51,730
Knock it off.

424
00:19:53,350 --> 00:19:54,030
Father,

425
00:19:54,030 --> 00:19:55,440
didn't you always tell me

426
00:19:55,440 --> 00:19:56,550
to judge things based on evidence?

427
00:19:56,550 --> 00:19:57,920
Guihong has no real proof now.

428
00:19:57,920 --> 00:20:00,580
How can you just decide
to punish Heng like that?

429
00:20:00,830 --> 00:20:02,440
Weren't you the one who kept demanding

430
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:03,640
I deal with Heng?

431
00:20:04,310 --> 00:20:05,830
I'm helping you.

432
00:20:06,440 --> 00:20:07,030
I...

433
00:20:09,590 --> 00:20:10,370
Father,

434
00:20:10,590 --> 00:20:12,480
this isn't the kind of help I want.

435
00:20:12,590 --> 00:20:14,000
It's because you always play favorites

436
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:15,030
that the whole world mocks me,

437
00:20:15,030 --> 00:20:16,160
saying I'm just a clueless fool

438
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:18,360
who only knows how to rely on his father.

439
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:27,000
Are you…

440
00:20:28,830 --> 00:20:29,960
blaming me?

441
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:31,270
I...

442
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:37,350
I'm blaming myself.

443
00:20:38,480 --> 00:20:39,160
Father.

444
00:20:39,750 --> 00:20:40,350
I know

445
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:42,390
I was too reckless before,

446
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,660
and I made things hard for you.

447
00:20:44,720 --> 00:20:46,250
But now I've figured it out.

448
00:20:47,440 --> 00:20:48,520
If Heng

449
00:20:48,590 --> 00:20:50,000
really is guilty,

450
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,720
then we should
investigate it openly and fairly

451
00:20:51,720 --> 00:20:53,180
and convict him properly.

452
00:20:53,680 --> 00:20:55,660
If you force a charge on him,

453
00:20:55,720 --> 00:20:58,240
sure, you might succeed
in stripping him of military command,

454
00:20:58,240 --> 00:20:59,960
but while you gain the command token,

455
00:20:59,960 --> 00:21:01,590
you'll lose the people's trust,

456
00:21:01,590 --> 00:21:02,580
Father!

457
00:21:08,350 --> 00:21:09,160
Again?

458
00:21:13,790 --> 00:21:15,050
I didn't arrange this.

459
00:21:17,510 --> 00:21:18,960
Alas!

460
00:21:19,070 --> 00:21:20,200
Fate is unfair sometimes,

461
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:21,510
but people never stop seeking justice.

462
00:21:21,510 --> 00:21:22,830
A centuries-old injustice

463
00:21:22,830 --> 00:21:24,160
finally sees the light.

464
00:21:24,160 --> 00:21:25,350
20,000 loyal souls

465
00:21:25,350 --> 00:21:26,880
lost to one man's betrayal.

466
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:28,200
Justice above family ties.

467
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:30,530
I, Yao Qian, come with evidence of crimes.

468
00:21:32,240 --> 00:21:33,830
What is he rambling about?

469
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:36,050
Bureaucratic mumbo jumbo,

470
00:21:36,050 --> 00:21:37,510
full of nonsense.

471
00:21:38,750 --> 00:21:39,750
Minister Yan.

472
00:21:40,240 --> 00:21:41,440
You have a letter too?

473
00:21:41,830 --> 00:21:42,790
Minister Yan,

474
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:44,860
General Chu, please listen to me.

475
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:46,920
While I was in the prince's study,

476
00:21:46,920 --> 00:21:48,450
I accidentally came across

477
00:21:48,590 --> 00:21:50,160
letters exchanged

478
00:21:50,160 --> 00:21:51,940
between Nan Heng and Heyuan.

479
00:21:51,710 --> 00:21:53,560
[Diligence for the People]

480
00:21:52,810 --> 00:21:55,290
Ministers, please take a look.

481
00:21:55,550 --> 00:21:56,470
Mr. Yao,

482
00:21:56,830 --> 00:21:59,320
treason is a capital offense.

483
00:21:59,550 --> 00:22:01,200
You'd better not be making this up.

484
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:02,470
I'm not.

485
00:22:02,990 --> 00:22:04,750
I'm a principled scholar.

486
00:22:04,790 --> 00:22:06,880
I study the classics
for the good of the world.

487
00:22:06,880 --> 00:22:09,120
Now, witnessing such injustice,

488
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:10,790
I'm willing to risk my life

489
00:22:10,790 --> 00:22:11,790
and turn against my own kin

490
00:22:11,790 --> 00:22:13,720
just for a fair judgment.

491
00:22:20,960 --> 00:22:21,830
Yao Qian.

492
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:24,590
You should know

493
00:22:25,440 --> 00:22:27,240
the consequences of framing me.

494
00:22:28,870 --> 00:22:30,340
This

495
00:22:30,440 --> 00:22:32,800
is the evidence I've prepared for you.

496
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:35,000
Tomorrow, His Majesty will issue an edict

497
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:38,030
for the Ministry of Justice
to try the Seventh Prince

498
00:22:38,030 --> 00:22:40,270
for hiring assassins to kill the witness.

499
00:22:40,270 --> 00:22:41,540
[Your Highness]

500
00:22:40,440 --> 00:22:42,270
This case is of great importance.

501
00:22:42,270 --> 00:22:44,470
You'll show up and testify against him.

502
00:22:45,070 --> 00:22:46,240
Chancellor,

503
00:22:46,380 --> 00:22:49,110
if I betray him like this,

504
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:50,680
he'll never let me off.

505
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:52,960
If you refuse to testify,

506
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:55,350
then you're betraying me.

507
00:22:55,670 --> 00:22:57,390
Mr. Yao, don't be afraid.

508
00:22:57,790 --> 00:22:59,200
You're standing up for the Qianyu Army.

509
00:22:59,200 --> 00:23:00,190
That's a righteous act.

510
00:23:00,190 --> 00:23:01,680
No matter what happens,

511
00:23:01,790 --> 00:23:03,590
His Majesty will have your back.

512
00:23:03,680 --> 00:23:05,210
We have solid evidence now.

513
00:23:05,640 --> 00:23:06,440
Guards!

514
00:23:06,930 --> 00:23:08,530
Arrest the criminal Nan Heng

515
00:23:08,750 --> 00:23:10,000
and take him to prison!

516
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:10,990
Wait.

517
00:23:11,160 --> 00:23:12,550
You're all conspiring

518
00:23:12,550 --> 00:23:13,920
to frame him!

519
00:23:14,070 --> 00:23:14,960
Minister Yan,

520
00:23:15,030 --> 00:23:16,360
don't be fooled by them.

521
00:23:18,680 --> 00:23:21,000
His Majesty has spoken.

522
00:23:21,860 --> 00:23:23,610
[Diligence for the People]

523
00:23:29,010 --> 00:23:32,750
Nan Heng, commander of the Xuanjia Army,
colluded with Heyuan

524
00:23:32,920 --> 00:23:34,480
and committed treason.

525
00:23:34,480 --> 00:23:36,070
His crime is unforgivable.

526
00:23:36,070 --> 00:23:40,180
The Three Bureaus
are to put Nan Heng in prison

527
00:23:40,310 --> 00:23:42,170
and await further instructions.

528
00:23:52,840 --> 00:23:53,620
Nan Heng.

529
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:55,830
You asked me to trust you once,

530
00:23:55,830 --> 00:23:56,590
and I did.

531
00:23:56,590 --> 00:23:58,000
But why would you confess

532
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:59,530
to something you didn't do?

533
00:24:00,720 --> 00:24:01,980
As long as you trust me,

534
00:24:02,750 --> 00:24:03,610
that's enough.

535
00:24:05,720 --> 00:24:06,240
But...

536
00:24:09,230 --> 00:24:09,990
Nan Heng.

537
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:14,830
Nan Heng!

538
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:26,010
[Song Residence]

539
00:24:28,480 --> 00:24:29,830
Even if the sky falls,

540
00:24:29,850 --> 00:24:31,340
you still need to eat.

541
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:34,440
No.

542
00:24:35,070 --> 00:24:36,500
Nan Heng's in prison now.

543
00:24:36,550 --> 00:24:38,820
Chu Guihong could kill him at any time.

544
00:24:38,880 --> 00:24:40,480
I have to get him out of there.

545
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:42,350
Don't blame yourself.

546
00:24:42,790 --> 00:24:44,090
You've done everything

547
00:24:44,090 --> 00:24:45,370
you could to help him.

548
00:24:49,030 --> 00:24:50,360
I'm not blaming myself.

549
00:24:51,110 --> 00:24:52,240
I just don't want

550
00:24:53,480 --> 00:24:55,210
the whole world to slander him.

551
00:25:01,030 --> 00:25:03,010
[Jinyang Mutiny] [Battle of Tancheng]

552
00:25:02,110 --> 00:25:03,070
What are these?

553
00:25:06,830 --> 00:25:07,790
These are

554
00:25:08,440 --> 00:25:09,920
the good deeds he has done.

555
00:25:11,110 --> 00:25:13,220
Four years ago, during the Jinyang Mutiny,

556
00:25:13,220 --> 00:25:14,750
when the Qianyu Army
stepped aside and did nothing,

557
00:25:14,750 --> 00:25:16,720
he led the Xuanjia Army
and fought for seven straight days

558
00:25:16,720 --> 00:25:18,050
to quell the rebellion.

559
00:25:18,240 --> 00:25:19,160
Five years ago,

560
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:20,650
the Battle of Tancheng.

561
00:25:20,650 --> 00:25:21,680
Ten years ago,

562
00:25:21,750 --> 00:25:23,660
in the all-out war with Dongshuo,

563
00:25:23,720 --> 00:25:25,640
if Nan Heng hadn't charged into battle,

564
00:25:25,640 --> 00:25:28,570
how could we have had
ten years of peace at the border?

565
00:25:31,640 --> 00:25:33,170
He told me all this long ago,

566
00:25:33,590 --> 00:25:35,390
but I didn't take him seriously.

567
00:25:44,350 --> 00:25:46,060
You saw what happened today.

568
00:25:46,640 --> 00:25:48,840
Chu Guihong has His Majesty behind him.

569
00:25:49,590 --> 00:25:50,880
The two of them are dead set

570
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:52,210
on taking Nan Heng down.

571
00:25:52,830 --> 00:25:54,890
As long as he hands over
the command token,

572
00:25:54,890 --> 00:25:56,680
they'll spare his life.

